description.narrative: UNICEF contributed to scaling up the School Based Management programme to 1,397 schoolsbenefiting 442,340 children.In 2021, UNICEF also supported a blended approach for teacher training, reaching 10,537 teachers (4,587 women) with training on Psychosocial Support (PSS), Positive Discipline (PD) and improved pedagogy. As part of the ECE approach, 412 pre-primary teachers from 137 schools were trained in delivering KG curriculum.Thanks to UNICEF’s support, 16,600 vulnerable youth (7,138 girls) were provided with access to skills-development opportunities. Out of the total 567 youths (243 girls) received seed funding and implemented social/business entrepreneurship initiatives benefitting their peers and communities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
